Overall, this was a fun trip. I got to spend a lot of time with family. Charlie had some problems with walking since he was limping, but overall he was able to make it through the trip without any problems. McAllen was very interesting - it is a food desert despite all the local agriculture south of the border. There was also a lot of border patrol presence. Corpus Christi was definitely more straightforward. It wasn't too big, and was basically centered on tourism. The photos are below. The photos from the trip are #link("https://photos.app.goo.gl/UUizKg6H1iEy8XSZ7")[here]
